underlying_goal: Resolve the statistical methodology for bootstrap SEM and implement the agreed-upon 'full pipeline bootstrap' to correctly capture all sources of variance.
primary_success: Orchestrating the consultation between data-analyst and research-advisor agents to converge on the principled 'bootstrap the entire pipeline' approach, and then correctly implementing this complex statistical procedure in the codebase.
brief_summary: Continuing from the previous session's discovery that the main experiment mode lacked variance reporting, the user and agent engaged specialist sub-agents (data-analyst, research-advisor) to determine the most statistically principled approach. After converging on 'bootstrap the entire pipeline', the agent implemented this feature for both split and k-fold CV modes, and updated all relevant documentation.
